@startuml
participant User
participant "Mobile App / Wallet" as App #lightblue
participant "Backend CoreAPI Middleware" as Backend #lightgreen
participant "Credential Platform Procivis Core" as Core #orange
participant "HSM" as HSM #yellow
participant "Government API Source of Truth" as OrgAPI #lightgray
participant "Trust Registry ETDA" as Trust #violet

note over Core,HSM #lightyellow:Issuer signing keys are HSM-backed\nPrivate key is generated inside HSM\nPrivate key never leaves HSM\nCore stores key metadata and HSM reference\nBackend receives ISSUER_KEY_ID and publicKey only

note over User,App #lightblue: 1.1 User Login and Consent
User->App: Login
App-->User: Show consent purpose, terms, version, expiry
User->App: Accept consent

note over App,Backend #lightblue: 1.2 Request VC Issuance
App->Backend: Request to add card / document\n(with consent acceptance evidence)

Backend->Backend: Store consent evidence

note right of Backend #lightyellow:purpose = issuance card/document\nconsentVersion\nconsentExpiry\nconsentTimestamp\ntermsReference\nuserId\ncitizenId\nconsentStatus = ACCEPTED

note over Backend #lightgreen: 1.3 Validate Existing Identity Assurance

Backend->Backend: Load existing identity assurance profile

note right of Backend #lightyellow:identityAssuranceId\ncitizenId\nIAL level\nAAL level\nKYC source\nKYC timestamp\nassurance expiry\nlast authentication method\nlast authentication timestamp

Backend->Backend: Validate assurance still valid\nand meets required freshness

alt Assurance invalid / expired / insufficient
    Backend-->App: Request step-up verification or re-KYC
    App-->User: Complete additional verification
    App->Backend: Submit verification result
    Backend->Backend: Update identity assurance profile
    Backend->Backend: Continue to Trust Validation
else Assurance valid
    Backend->Backend: Continue to Trust Validation
end

note right of Backend #lightyellow :Use user session\nuserId\ncitizenId\naccess token

note over Backend,Trust #violet: 2. Trust Framework Validation
Backend->Trust: Validate issuer eligibility and schema policy
Trust-->Backend: Trust status policy LoA requirement

Backend->Backend: Store trust validation result , policy version, timestamp\ntrust registry reference, LoA requirement

Backend->Backend: Validate issuer allowed & schema approved & LoA sufficient & consent valid

alt Trust validation failed
    Backend->Backend: Update status TRUST_FAILED
    Backend-->App: Reject issuance request
    App-->User: Cannot proceed
else Trust validation passed
    Backend->Backend: Continue issuance
end

note over Backend,OrgAPI #lightgray: 3. Fetch Official card / document
Backend->OrgAPI: GET  card / document info from org

note right of OrgAPI #lightyellow:Retrieve official card/document data\nfrom government source of truth

OrgAPI-->Backend:  card / document info

Backend->Backend: Store source data freshness and cache policy

note right of Backend #lightyellow:sourceFetchedAt = current timestamp\nsourceLastUpdatedAt = from OrgAPI if available\nsourceSystem = Government API Source of Truth\ncachePolicy = no-cache / short-lived cache\ncacheTTL = e.g. 5 minutes\ncacheKey = citizenId + documentType\ncacheInvalidation = on revoke / suspend / expire

Backend->Backend: Validate official data & Check status active & Check not suspended &\nCheck not revoked etc.

alt Official card/document invalid
    Backend->Backend: Update status SOURCE_DATA_INVALID
    Backend-->App: Reject issuance request
    App-->User: card/document not eligible
else Official card/document valid
    Backend->Backend: Prepare verified claims
end

note over Backend #lightyellow: 4. Prepare Data
Backend->Backend: Validate and prepare data

Backend->Backend: Create tamper-proof audit record

note right of Backend #lightyellow:auditHash = hash(canonical audit payload)\nauditSignature = sign(auditHash)\npreviousAuditHash = link to previous log\nretentionPolicy = e.g. 10 years or regulatory requirement\nretentionUntil = issuedAt + retention period\nimmutableStorage = WORM / append-only log

note right of Backend #lightyellow:Store issuance request\nStore mapped claims\nStore audit log\nStore identity assurance reference\nStore consent evidence

note over Backend,Core #orange: 5. Setup Issuer One Time or Reuse
Backend->Core: Create or get organization\n(POST /api/organisation/v1)
Core-->Backend: Organization ID (ORG_ID) or error

alt Create/Get organization failed
    Backend->Backend: Update status = ISSUER_SETUP_FAILED
    Backend->Backend: Store issuer setup failure audit log

    note right of Backend #pink:failureStep = CREATE_OR_GET_ORGANIZATION\nerrorCode\nerrorMessage\nretryable = true/false\nfailedAt\nissuanceSessionId\nuserId\ncitizenId

    Backend-->App: Reject issuance request\nreason = ISSUER_SETUP_FAILED
    App-->User: Cannot proceed at this time
else Organization ready
    Backend->Backend: Store ORG_ID\nReuse for future issuance

    Backend->Core: Create issuer signing key (POST /api/key/v1)\n(keyType, storageType = HSM-backed, organisationId)
    Core->HSM: Generate issuer signing key\n(non-exportable private key)
    HSM-->Core: HSM key reference + public key
    Core-->Backend: Issuer Key ID (ISSUER_KEY_ID), publicKey or error
            
    alt Create issuer signing key failed
        Backend->Backend: Update status = ISSUER_KEY_SETUP_FAILED
        Backend->Backend: Store issuer key failure audit log

        note right of Backend #pink:failureStep = CREATE_ISSUER_SIGNING_KEY\nORG_ID\nerrorCode\nerrorMessage\nhsmErrorReference\nretryable = true/false\nfailedAt\nissuanceSessionId

        Backend-->App: Reject issuance request\nreason = ISSUER_KEY_SETUP_FAILED
        App-->User: Cannot proceed at this time
    else Issuer key ready

note right of Backend #lightyellow: Store ISSUER_KEY_ID\nStore publicKey\nStore key algorithm\nStore key status = ACTIVE\nDo not store HSM_KEY_REF if managed by Core\nDo not expose key to mobile app
        Backend->Core: Create issuer identity or DID (POST /api/identifier/v1)\n(reference ISSUER_KEY_ID)
        note right of Core #lightyellow:DID can have multiple keys (verification methods)\nInitial key is used at creation\nAdditional keys can be added via identifier update API\nKeys can be rotated without changing DID

        Core-->Backend: Issuer Identity ID (ISSUER_IDENTIFIER_ID) or error

        alt Create issuer identity / DID failed
            Backend->Backend: Update status = ISSUER_IDENTIFIER_SETUP_FAILED
            Backend->Backend: Store issuer identifier failure audit log

            note right of Backend #pink:failureStep = CREATE_ISSUER_IDENTIFIER\nORG_ID\nISSUER_KEY_ID\nerrorCode\nerrorMessage\nretryable = true/false\nfailedAt\nissuanceSessionId

            Backend->Backend: Mark ISSUER_KEY_ID as UNUSED_SETUP_FAILED\nor keep for retry according to key policy

            Backend-->App: Reject issuance request\nreason = ISSUER_IDENTIFIER_SETUP_FAILED
            App-->User: Cannot proceed at this time
        else Issuer identifier ready
            Backend->Backend: Store ISSUER_IDENTIFIER_ID\nBind issuer DID with ISSUER_KEY_ID\nCore manages HSM key reference internally

            Backend->Backend: Update issuance status = READY_FOR_HOLDER_BINDING

            Backend-->App: Issuance pre-check passed\nnextAction = PREPARE_HOLDER_WALLET\nissuanceSessionId
        end
    end
end

note over App,Core #orange: 6. Prepare Holder Wallet and DID Binding

App->Backend: Request holder key registration challenge\n(issuanceSessionId)
Backend-->App: challengeId, nonce, expiresAt

note right of Backend #lightyellow: Proof of Possession\nchallenge purpose = holder_key_binding\nchallenge expiresAt\nchallenge used = false\nchallenge bound to userId + deviceId + issuanceSessionId\nprevent replay attack

note over App #lightblue: Prepare holder key on device
alt Holder key exists on device
    App->App: Load holder private key\nfrom Secure Enclave / Android Keystore / StrongBox
else First time / key not found
    App->App: Generate holder key pair\n(Secure Enclave / Android Keystore / StrongBox)
end

App->App: Sign challenge with holder private key

App->Backend: Submit holder proof\n(signedChallenge, challengeId, publicKey)
Backend->Backend: Validate user session & Validate device binding &\nVerify signed challenge using public key

alt Holder key proof invalid
    Backend->Backend: Update status HOLDER_KEY_BINDING_FAILED
    Backend-->App: Reject holder binding
    App-->User: Cannot prepare wallet
else Holder key proof valid
    Backend->Backend: Mark challenge as used
    Backend->Core: Create holder identity or DID\n(POST /api/identifier/v1 with publicKey)
    Core-->Backend: Holder Identity ID (HOLDER_IDENTIFIER_ID)
    
note right of Backend #lightyellow:Store HOLDER_IDENTIFIER_ID\nStore holder public key reference\nStore key type / algorithm\nStore deviceId\nLink with userId/deviceId\nDo not store holder private key

    Backend->Backend: Bind citizenId to holder identifier\nBind holder identifier to user account\nBind holder identifier to trusted device
    
    Backend->Backend: Update issuance status = HOLDER_BOUND

    Backend-->App: Holder binding completed\nstatus = HOLDER_BOUND\nnextAction = WAIT_FOR_CREDENTIAL_OFFER

    Backend->Backend: Trigger next step (internal)\nevent = HOLDER_BINDING_SUCCESS
end

note over Backend,Core #orange: 7. Define Digital Card/Document Schema and Lifecycle Policy

Backend->Backend: Continue issuance\n(triggered by HOLDER_BINDING_SUCCESS)

Backend->Core: Get or create card/document schema\n(GET/POST /api/credential-schema/v1)
Core-->Backend: Credential Schema ID (CREDENTIAL_SCHEMA_ID)

Backend->Backend: Store schema versioning and compatibility policy

note right of Backend #lightyellow:schemaVersion = v1.0.0\nschemaStatus = ACTIVE\ncredentialType = DigitalDrivingLicense\nbackwardCompatibility = supported\ncompatibleVersions = v1.x\nbreakingChangePolicy = create new schema ID\nmigrationPolicy = support old credentials until expiry\ndeprecationPolicy = announce and sunset by date

note right of Backend #lightyellow:Store CREDENTIAL_SCHEMA_ID\nStore schema version\nStore credential type

Backend->Core: Get schema details (GET /api/credential-schema/v1/{id})
Core-->Backend: Claim IDs

note right of Backend #lightyellow :Map fields to claim IDs\nlicense number\nlicense type\nissue date\nexpiry date\nholder name\ncitizenId\nissuing authority

Backend->Backend: Set credential metadata & validFrom & validUntil &\nrevocation status method & credential lifecycle policy

Backend->Core: Get issuer key metadata\nGET /api/key/v1/{ISSUER_KEY_ID}
Core-->Backend: key status, createdAt, expiresAt

alt Key expired / near expiry / inactive
    Backend->Core: Create new issuer signing key (POST /api/key/v1)\n(keyType, storageType = HSM-backed, organisationId)

    Core->HSM: Generate new issuer signing key\n(non-exportable private key)
    HSM-->Core: HSM key reference + public key
    Core-->Backend: New ISSUER_KEY_ID, publicKey

    Backend->Core: Update issuer DID / identifier (PATCH /api/identifier/v1/{ISSUER_IDENTIFIER_ID})
    note right of Core #lightyellow:Add new key as verification method\nMark old key as deprecated\nKeep old key for verification of existing credentials

    Core-->Backend: Updated issuer identifier

    Backend->Backend: Mark old ISSUER_KEY_ID as DEPRECATED
    note right of Backend #lightyellow:Keep old ISSUER_KEY_ID available for verifying previously issued credentials\nOld key status = DEPRECATED, not revoked\nUse new ISSUER_KEY_ID for new credential issuance only\nRevoke old key only if compromised
    
else Key active
    Backend->Backend: Continue issuance
end

note over Backend,Core #orange: 8. Create Digital Credential and Offer
Backend->Core: Create digital credential (POST /api/credential/v1)
Core-->Backend: Credential ID (CREDENTIAL_ID)

note right of Backend #lightyellow:Store CREDENTIAL_ID\nStatus CREATED

Backend->Core: Generate secure pickup link (POST /api/credential/{id}/share)
Core-->Backend: Credential Offer URL

note right of Backend #lightyellow: Store OFFER_URL (temporary)

Backend-->App: Send offer link

note over App,Core #orange: 9. User Receives Credential Offer
App->Backend: Open credential offer

Backend->Core: Handle invitation (POST /api/interaction/v1/handle-invitation)
Core-->Backend: INTERACTION_ID and credential preview

Backend-->App: Return preview

note right of App #lightyellow:Store INTERACTION_ID temporary\nShow issuer\nShow claims\nShow expiry\nShow terms

note over User,App #lightblue: 10. User Reviews Credential
App-->User: Show digital card/document preview

alt Holder accepts credential
    User->App: Accept
    App->Backend: Confirm acceptance

note over Backend,Core #orange: 11A. Issue Credential
Backend->Core: Accept credential\n(POST /api/interaction/v1/issuance-accept)
Core-->Backend: Credential issued

Backend->Backend: Update status ACCEPTED & Update status ISSUED

Backend->Backend: Store signed issuance audit log

note right of Backend #lightyellow:eventType = CREDENTIAL_ISSUED\ncredentialId\nissuedAt\nissuer identifier\nholder identifier\ncredential status reference\nauditHash\nauditSignature\nretentionUntil

note over Backend #lightgreen: 11A.1 Remote Credential Storage Model

Backend->Backend: Confirm credential is stored in Procivis Core\nCore is source of truth for VC payload
Backend->Backend: Do not persist full VC payload in Backend\nStore credential reference only
Backend->Backend: Store credentialId = CREDENTIAL_ID\nStore holderIdentifierId = HOLDER_IDENTIFIER_ID\nStore issuerIdentifierId = ISSUER_IDENTIFIER_ID\nStore schemaId = CREDENTIAL_SCHEMA_ID\nStore credential type\nStore credential status reference\nStore validFrom / validUntil\nStore storageMode = REMOTE_CORE

note right of Backend #lightyellow:Remote credential model\nVC payload remains in Procivis Core\nBackend stores references and metadata only\nMobile stores references and display metadata only\nFull VC payload is fetched only during VP preparation after consent

note over Backend #lightgreen: 11A.2 Prepare Credential Reference Package for Mobile

Backend->Backend: Prepare credential reference package\ncredentialId\ncredentialType\nissuer DID / issuer display name\nschemaId\nvalidFrom / validUntil\ncredential status reference\ndisplay metadata\nstorageMode = REMOTE_REFERENCE\npresentationMode = BACKEND_ASSISTED_MOBILE_SIGNED

note over Backend,App #lightgreen: 11A.3 Send Credential Reference to Mobile Wallet

Backend-->App: Credential reference package\ncredentialId\ncredentialType\nissuer DID / issuer display name\nschemaId\nvalidFrom / validUntil\ncredential status reference\ndisplay metadata\nstorageMode = REMOTE_REFERENCE\npresentationMode = BACKEND_ASSISTED_MOBILE_SIGNED

note over App #lightgreen: 11A.4 Mobile Wallet Stores Credential Reference Only

App->App: Store credentialId only\nDo not store full VC payload
App->App: Store credential metadata\ncredentialType\nissuer DID / issuer display name\nschemaId\nvalidFrom / validUntil\nstatus reference\ndisplay metadata
App->App: Bind credentialId to HOLDER_IDENTIFIER_ID\nBind credentialId to deviceId\nBind credentialId to holder key reference
App->App: Mark credential as available for presentation\npresentationMode = BACKEND_ASSISTED_MOBILE_SIGNED\nstorageMode = REMOTE_REFERENCE

note right of App #lightyellow:Mobile Wallet does not keep VC payload\nMobile keeps only credential reference + metadata\nHolder private key remains on device\nCredential payload will be retrieved by Backend from Core during VP flow after Holder consent

note over App #lightgreen: 11A.5 Secure Local Reference Storage and Access Policy

App->App: Store credential reference in secure local storage\nEncryptedSharedPreferences / Room encrypted DB / Keychain
App->App: Protect reference access with device security\nbiometric / PIN / device unlock
App->App: Prevent export of holder private key\nSecure Enclave / Android Keystore / StrongBox
App->App: Configure usage policy\nrequire consent before presentation\nrequire holder signing before VP submission

note over App,Backend #lightgreen: 11A.6 Mobile confirms credential reference storage

App->Backend: Confirm credential reference stored\ncredentialId\nstorageStatus = STORED_REFERENCE\nholderIdentifierId\ndeviceId\ntimestamp

note over Backend #lightgreen: 11A.7 Backend Records Remote Storage Audit Log

Backend->Backend: Store remote credential reference audit log\ncredentialId\nholderIdentifierId\nissuerIdentifierId\nschemaId\ndeviceId\nstorageMode = REMOTE_CORE\nmobileStorageMode = REMOTE_REFERENCE\nissuedAt\nstoredReferenceAt\nauditHash\nauditSignature\npreviousAuditHash\nretentionUntil

Backend-->App: Credential reference storage acknowledged\nstatus = STORED_REFERENCE

App-->User: Show digital card/document\nrendered from local metadata and remote credential reference

else Holder rejects credential
    User->App: Reject
    App->Backend: Send rejection

    note over Backend #pink: 11B. Handle Holder Reject
    Backend->Backend: Update status HOLDER_REJECTED

Backend->Backend: Create tamper-proof rejection audit log

note right of Backend #pink:eventType = CREDENTIAL_REJECTED\ncredentialId\ninteractionId\nuserId\nholderIdentifierId\nissuerIdentifierId\nrejectionReason\nrejectedAt\nauditHash\nauditSignature\npreviousAuditHash\nretentionUntil\nimmutableStorage = WORM / append-only

    Backend-->App: Cancel issuance
    App-->User: Credential not issued
end
@enduml
